OL,5,FChannel 4 has commissioned a range of
OL,6,Fedgy programmes as part of a 40th
OL,7,Fanniversary season which are not about
OL,8,FChannel 4 or the anniversary itself.
OL,10,FThis is actually in keeping with the
OL,11,Fchannel's early personality ` offering,
OL,12,Ffor example, Christmas programmes which
OL,13,Fcontrasted with the explicitly festive
OL,14,Fofferings elsewhere.
OL,16,FBut then again today's Channel 4 is not
OL,17,Fthe channel of the 80s and 90s even if
OL,18,Fit's more distinctive parts speak to
OL,19,Fits roots.
OL,3,CBBC and Channel 4 in celebration mode
